When you create a new repository, the instructions for cloning it give you a different URL than the "Clone" button

The Clone button at the top-right gives me this URL, which is what I want:

{quote}
ssh://git@scm.ctisl.gtri.gatech.edu/~cmartin34/test.git
{quote}

When I create a new repository, the instruction page says:

{quote}
If you want to simply clone this empty repository then run this command in your terminal.
git clone https://cmartin34@scm.ctisl.gtri.gatech.edu/git/scm/~cmartin34/test.git
{quote}

This second address is useless to me - I think it should give the same URL that the Clone button gives.

*Rating*: :( Bad

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
I like that this page gives me the exact commands, customized for my repo, that I need to run to add my code to the newly created repo.

In a more general sense, I like that it's quick and easy to create personal repos.
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
It really bugs me that this page only explains how to clone over HTTP, rather than SSH. I'm not too keen on having to type my password to authenticate every time I push/pull/fetch, etc -- that's what SSH keys are for!

I know that I can get the SSH URL from the Clone dialog, but it isn't displayed very prominently. In fact, I didn't notice it until I was fact-checking this feedback. ;)
{panel}

